import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.hist(data['price'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of price?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.title('What is the trend of price over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['symbol'] = data['symbol'].astype(str)
    avg_price_by_symbol = data.groupby('symbol')['price'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(avg_price_by_symbol['symbol'], avg_price_by_symbol['price'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Symbol')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the average price by symbol?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'] = pd.to_numeric(data['price'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['price'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['symbol'], data['price'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Symbol')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between symbol and price?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['date'], bins=50, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of dates?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
